A.D.T.
array:
  1) decleration (type[] name;)
  2) initialitaziotion  (new type[size];)
  3) combine them with (type[] name = new type[size];)

array features:
  1) arrays are zero based
  2) arrays have a length property which is equal to the size of the array
  3) all elements must be of the same type
  4) direct acess
  5) contiguous memory allowcation
  6) fixed in size (cannot shrink or enlarge)
